The '''1969 [[Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup|National Challenge Cup]]''' was the 56th edition of the United States Soccer Football Association's annual open soccer championship. The [[Greek American AA]] team defeated the [[Montebello Armenians]] in the final game. As a result, Greek American Atlas won their third consecutive National Cup title. The feat would not be repeated until [[2011 U.S. Open Cup Final|2011]], when [[Seattle Sounders FC|Seattle Sounders]] defeated [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Seattle Sounders Win Third Consecutive Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup in Front of Record Crowd |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Lamar-Hunt-U-S-Open-Cup/2011/10/Seattle-Sounders-Claim-Third-Consecutive-Open-Cup-Title.aspx |publisher=U.S. Soccer |accessdate=October 5, 2011 |date=October 4, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120121035705/http://www.ussoccer.com/News/Lamar-Hunt-U-S-Open-Cup/2011/10/Seattle-Sounders-Claim-Third-Consecutive-Open-Cup-Title.aspx |archivedate=January 21, 2012 |df= }}</ref>
