{{about|the cricket ground|the former rugby union, speedway and greyhound racing venue|County Ground Stadium}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Use British English|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = County Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = Entrance gate to the County Ground, Exeter (geograph 5245056).jpg | caption = Entrance gates to the County Ground | location = [[Exeter]], [[Devon]] | establishment = 1889 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1902&ndash;1987 | club1 = [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]] | date = 24 July | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/472.html Ground profile }}
The '''County Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Exeter]], [[Devon]]. The earliest recorded match on the ground was in 1889 between the Gentlemen of Devon and [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/472_misc.html Other matches played on County Ground]</ref> In 1902, [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]] played their first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match on the ground, which came against [[Wiltshire County Cricket Club|Wiltshire]]. From 1902 to 1987, the ground played host to 148 Minor Counties Championship matches<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/472_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on the County Ground]</ref> and a single [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] match between Devon and [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]] in 1984.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/472_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on the County Ground]</ref> The ground hosted its first Minor Counties match in 23 years in May 2010, when Devon played [[Wales Minor Counties Cricket Club|Wales Minor Counties]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/266/266209.html Devon v Wales Minor Counties, 2010]</ref>
The ground has hosted a 2 [[first-class cricket|first-class]] matches, the first of which came in 1927, when the West played the touring [[New Zealand national cricket team|New Zealanders]]. The second and final first-class match played on the ground came the following year, when a combined [[Minor Counties cricket team]] played the touring [[West Indies cricket team|West Indians]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/472_f.html First-Class Matches played the County Ground]</ref>
The only [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match played on the ground came in the [[1980 Gillette Cup]] between Devon and [[Cornwall County Cricket Club|Cornwall]], which Devon won by 145 runs.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/472_a.html List-A Matches played on the County Ground]</ref>
[[File:University of Exeter, Streatham Campus - geograph.org.uk - 1004242.jpg|thumb|The University of Exeter, with the County Ground at the top centre of image]]In local domestic cricket, the County Ground is the home ground of [[Exeter Cricket Club]] who play in the [[Devon Cricket League]]. The club has played at the ground for over 180 years.<ref>[http://exeter.play-cricket.com/home/aboutUs.asp Exeter Cricket Club] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120710202302/http://exeter.play-cricket.com/home/aboutUs.asp |date=2012-07-10 }}</ref>
