The '''Enyimba International Stadium''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Aba, Nigeria|Aba]], [[Nigeria]].  It is currently used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches. It serves as a home ground of [[Enyimba International F.C.]] The stadium holds 16,000 people.<ref>http://www.nairaland.com/3034593/governor-okezie-ikpeazu-contributes-new</ref> On November 3, 2008 the stadium received a temporary ban after the home crowd attacked referees after a heated 1-1 tie with rivals [[Heartland F.C.]].<ref>[http://www.tribune.com.ng/04112008/news/sports3.html]</ref>

