'''Motor Racing Outreach''' is a [[Nondenominational Christianity|non-denominational Christian Protestant]] organization that serves the [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series]], NASCAR [[Xfinity Series]], and various other levels and forms of motor sports across the [[United States]].

==History==
Motor Racing Outreach (MRO) is a [[non-profit organization]] founded in 1988 to serve the NASCAR Sprint Cup racing community. Motor Racing Outreach was founded by Max Helton <ref>http://autoracingsport.com/motor-racing-outreach-founder-max-helton-dies/</ref> in response to a need presented by 3 drivers within the [[NASCAR Sprint Cup Series]] who were unable to attend regular church services due to the demands on their schedule.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ministrywatch.com/profile/motor-racing-outreach.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120905110114/http://www.ministrywatch.com/profile/motor-racing-outreach.aspx |archivedate=2012-09-05 |df= }}</ref>

